Q1:
Introduction

This study is conducted by student researchers in Computational Social Science at the University of Amsterdam (UvA) and in partnership with the Municipality of Amsterdam. 

 

Goal of the study 

The aim of the study is to develop an interactive website focusing on water ecology management across global cities, providing accessible knowledge to a broad audience. The information gathered in this survey is needed to assess the level of awareness of the general public regarding water quality management within their city and globally. 

 

Procedure of the study 

If you agree to participate, you will be asked to take part in a survey. You will be asked several multiple-choice questions or statements. For each question or statement, you can indicate the extent to which you agree or disagree with something, or indicate which answer you think applies the most. There is also one open-ended question. We ask questions about your knowledge of water quality issues and your interest and preferences for a digital intervention regarding water management worldwide. 

 

Voluntary Participation 

Your participation in this study is voluntary: you are not obliged to participate. You may decide to stop your participation at any time during the study. 

 

Privacy 

Your responses will be kept confidential. All data will be securely stored and only accessible to the research team and directly relevant UvA instructors. No identifying information will be gathered through this survey; all data is anonymous. 

 

We use some third-party software to store and process your data. UvA has contracts with these parties to guarantee your privacy: 


	Your data will be securely stored with Microsoft OneDrive and/or Canvas.
	Your data will be processed by Qualtrics to store data, analyze data, collaborate, manage questionnaires, etc.

Further Information 

If you have any questions about the study, either before you participate or afterwards, please feel free to contact the responsible researcher: Célia Meissner, celia.meissner@student.uva.nl .



If you have any formal complaints about this research, please send an email to the UvA staff member supervising this project: Regina Nockerts, r.a.nockerts@uva.nl. The staff member that approved the study will consider your complaint and contact you as soon as possible.



Declaration of consent

With this you declare:

	I am 16 years or older.
	I have read and understood the information.
	I agree to participate in the study and to use the data obtained with it.
	I reserve the right to withdraw this consent without giving any reason.
	I reserve the right to stop the study at any time I wish.
